@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


Hello! Thanks for taking the time to read this...

The Lightwave particle animator or LWPA was origianlly delveloped in CLI form about a
year ago on the Amiga. It was then ported to  WindowsNT to run on my PC; none of these
versions were ever released, though... In the summer of 97 I decided to port it back
over to the Amiga which meant writing a front end and changing a few bits and bobs, so
here it is!

Oh yeah, I forgot the disclaimer: if LWPA blows up your computer, sends evil letters
to your gran or threatens world domination  then I take no responsibility. Use it at
your own risk.... A hem.


Having run a few limited speed comparisons I can say that LWPA is about @{b}9.5@{ub}(!!!) times
faster than Sparks at doing the same thing,  however Sparks has more features... But
then LWPA is far more  stable than Sparks! Ha.


If anyone is interested I can make the PC version of LWPA available at a minimal cost
of, say ú5?


If I manage to get hold of a PowerUp board for my 3000, then I will port LWPA over to
the PowerPC, coz it would be a hell of a lot quicker.

If you want to get in contact with me my address is:

